## BACKLOG (user: "don't forget the others")

### Outside-model prompt dogfeed  (transparency / cost audit)  ← NEW (user) · MEDIUM prio
Surface the prompts we send to **non-hosted** models (OpenRouter: feketecs flash,
anstetten pro) to a single VISIBLE place. Low overhead, fire-and-forget, never blocks
a run, never leaks the key. Target: **one rolling GitHub issue** ("oracle: outside-model
prompt dogfeed") — find-or-create, append ONE comment per run (max 1 issue).
- emit only outside-model (key_env-gated) calls; local qwen/llm4d stay off-feed
- per call: model · role(panel/judge) · prompt_sha + prompt first line · completion_tokens ·
  usage.cost — NOT full responses (noise/privacy); cap comment size
- non-blocking + best-effort (swallow failures); auth via `gh` (M3 has it) OR the
  social-post staging-file pattern (box writes artifact → CI posts; key never on box)
- complements (does not replace) Langfuse SDK push — this is the zero-infra, human-visible cut


### Slice 3 — agentic reverser → PROMOTED to active (see top). Chosen: hybrid
LLM-driven policy + crabcc-powered investigate. Off-the-shelf free-form agent CLIs
(claude/pi/nullclaw) deferred — the auditable LLM-policy middle ground won.

### Slice 4 — arbitrary-binary RE  (generality)
Unknown/stripped ELFs — the pure llm4decompile / OGhidra demo. Proves the system
works beyond the FOSS-ground-truth case. No ground truth ⇒ needs a confidence
heuristic to replace fidelity-vs-source scoring (self-consistency / recompile-diff).

### Slice 4b — thread 1 (team-in-vaked) — IN PROGRESS (branch feat/oracle-team-in-vaked)
oracle-team.vaked + roster_from_vaked (graph -> roster/judge/budget + egress drift check)
+ `team --from-vaked` + agent_guardd manifest interop. Follow-ups: vakedc E-EGRESS-USE
pass (RFC like 0027); local egress proxy for full OpenRouter packet attestation.
Next threads: 2 (RE-vakedz), 3 (ARP-emission, deferred — other dev's lane).

### Slice 4b — thread 2 (RE-vakedz) — DONE (branch feat/oracle-re-vakedz)
Recursive self-RE: oracle RE's our own vakedz Zig ELF (built on box via `nix shell nixpkgs#zig`,
Zig 0.16.0). Cross-language fidelity (C-vs-Zig) ~0.46-0.58 Dice (mean ~0.51) on
sha256Hex/chainHex/leqGrant — modestly below same-language. `run:vakedz` Taskfile (static).
Caveat: Zig dotted names -> Ghidra short names. Follow-up: tree-sitter-Zig AST fidelity (slice 5).
Next: thread 3 (ARP, deferred). Plus dogfeed (item 2, MEDIUM).

### Slice 5 — deepen target + fidelity  (hardening)
- ggml/tensor hot path: `ggml_compute_forward`, `ggml_graph_compute` on
  `libggml-base.so` (more llama.cpp surface for static+dynamic acceptance).
- tree-sitter AST fidelity replacing `normalized-token-similarity` in `fidelity.py`.
- widen the eBPF watcher trace window to catch GGUF mmap.

