### vakedc E-EGRESS-USE + W-EGRESS-UNREFINED — DONE (branch feat/vakedc-egress-use)
Network-membrane POLA in vakedc/check.py (dual of E-CAP-USE/W-POLA-EXCESS): a networkMembrane
may not authorize egress beyond its principal's network grant (E-EGRESS-USE error); unrefined
egress grant -> W-EGRESS-UNREFINED warning. Promotes thread-1 roster_from_vaked.check_roster_egress
to a language pass. Corpus-safe (0 new errors; advisory warning on 10 examples). docs/language/0026.
Follow-ups: RFC formalization; port to vakedz (Zig front-end).

### Network-membrane POLA formalization (0028) — DONE (branch feat/vakedz-egress-use)
docs/language/0028-network-membrane-pola.md: formalizes E-EGRESS-USE (allowed ⊑ granted, host→level
lattice, soundness as the network dual of 0027's used⊑granted, deny-by-default + the lower-time DNS gap)
AND specs the vakedz parity port. FINDING: vakedz/src/check.zig lacks the ENTIRE POLA-reachability layer
(no E-CAP-USE/W-POLA-EXCESS/membrane handling) — porting E-EGRESS-USE alone is incoherent; the parity
work is the whole reachability suite as its own WP (spec'd in 0028 §vakedz parity). Deferred: vakedz POLA
parity cycle; Lean obligation for E-EGRESS-USE (mirrors 0027).
